arize files changed and paste the verification output. Don't claim success without having\\nactually run the commands above in this worktree.\\n\"] --timeout-seconds 1500\n 735258 Sl   codex exec --sandbox workspace-write --cd /workspaces/agent-orchestrator/.orchestrator/worktrees/obs-persist-a1 --skip-git-repo-check --json -o /tmp/claude-0/-workspaces-agent-orchestrator/1c1c961b-6d61-41d6-848a-da60812c189f/scratchpad/task-obs-persist-lastmsg.txt # Task: persist process-lifecycle observations, not just log them  Repo: agent-orchestrator, backend/ (Python, hexagonal architecture — read CLAUDE.md at repo root first).  ## The gap (found in code review of a prior task)  `backend/src/infra/runtime/process_supervisor.py`'s `supervise_process()` already builds correct `TelemetryObservation` objects (via `app/observations.py`) for `PROCESS_STARTED` and `PROCESS_EXITED`/`PROCESS_TIMED_OUT`, and passes them to an `on_observation` callback. But the caller — `CliAgentRunner._run_sync` in `backend/src/infra/runtime/cli_runner.py` — only forwards them to `structlog` (`log.info(\"runtime.process_observation\", ...)`). Nothing persists them to the durable observation ledger, so they never reach `GET /api/metrics` or any other read model — they're diagnostic-log-only, not canonical evidence.  ## The existing pattern to copy  `backend/src/infra/reasoner/openai_reasoner.py` already does this correctly for reasoner usage: read it (constructor around line 270-300, the append call around line 330-340). It takes an optional `observation_repository: ObservationRepository | None = None` constructor parameter and calls `await self._observation_repository.append(observation)`. The composition root wires it in `backend/src/infra/container.py`'s `reasoner` cached property, passing `self.observation_repository` into `build_reasoner(...)`.  `build_agent_runner(...)` (same container.py, `agent_runner` cached property) does **not** currently receive `observation_repository` — only `orchestrator_home`. Extend it the same way `orchestrator_home` was threaded through in a prior task: `container.py` → `build_agent_runner` (`factory.py`) → `CatalogAgentRunner.__init__` → `CatalogAgentRunner._runner_for` → each `CliAgentRunner` subclass constructor (`PiAgentRunner`/`ClaudeCodeRunner`/`GeminiRunner`), same default-`None` optional-parameter style already used for `orchestrator_home`.  ## The sync/async boundary — read this carefully  `_run_sync` runs inside `asyncio.to_thread(self._run_sync, ...)` (see `CliAgentRunner.run()`) — it is a **synchronous** function running in a worker thread. `supervise_process`'s `on_observation` callback is invoked synchronously from within that same call (never from the reader threads — only the main supervisor flow calls it, at process start and at exit/timeout, so there's no concurrent-write hazard). You **cannot** `await` an async repository method from inside that synchronous callback.  The correct fix: have `_run_sync` collect the `TelemetryObservation` objects it receives into a plain list (a local list created by the caller and mutated in place, or however you find cleanest — it must survive both the success path and the `TaskFailed`-raising paths, since a timeout or non-zero exit still produces a `PROCESS_TIMED_OUT`/`PROCESS_EXITED` observation worth keeping). Back in the **async** `run()` method, after `await asyncio.to_thread(self._run_sync, ...)` completes (or raises `TaskFailed` — persist what was collected before re-raising), iterate the collected observations and `await self._observation_repository.append(observation)` for each, exactly like the reasoner does.  Persistence must be **best-effort and isolated from task success/failure** — matches the existing `event_sink` pattern in this same file (e.g. how `AgentEvent` emission never blocks or fails the task). If `self._observation_repository` is `None` (not configured, e.g. dry-run or a test double), skip persistence entirely — don't error. Wrap the persist loop so an exception while appending observations is logged (structlog) and swallowed, never propagated to fail an otherwise-successful task.  ## Constraints  - Do NOT touch `backend/src/domain/`. - Do NOT change the `AgentRunner` port's `run()` method signature — this is a constructor-level   dependency, not a per-call parameter (same reasoning as `orchestrator_home`). - Keep the existing `log.info(\"runtime.process_observation\", ...)` structlog call too — it's   still useful for live debugging; this task is additive (persist AND log), not replace-one-with-   the-other. - `mypy src` must stay clean. Follow existing code style.  ## Verification (run yourself; report exact output)  ``` cd backend ruff check src tests --fix mypy src pytest -m \"not integration\" -k \"cli_runner or process_supervisor or observation or reasoner or factory\" pytest -q ```  Write at least one focused test proving observations actually reach the repository (a fake/in- memory `ObservationRepository` — check `src/app/testing/` for an existing fake to reuse before writing a new one) for both the success path and a failure/timeout path. All commands must pass before you finish; the full suite (currently 453 passing, 5 skipped) must show zero regressions.  ## When done  Summarize files changed and paste the verification output. Don't claim success without having actually run the commands above in this worktree. \n 746324 Ss   /bin/bash -c kill -TERM 741429 742969 744640 741428 742963 744635 2>/dev/null || true; sleep 2; ps -eo pid,stat,cmd | rg '[p]ytest -q' || true; cd backend && timeout 180 pytest -q\n....................................ss.ss............................... [ 15%]\n...............s........................................................ [ 31%]\n........................................................................ [ 46%]\n........................................................................ [ 62%]\n........................................................................ [ 78%]\n......